{
  "style": "IEEE",
  "texts": [
    "CoT enhances performance on complex tasks by instructing the LLM to engage in step-by-step reasoning.",
    "In the context of test generation, this is typically implemented as a multi-stage process.",
    "For instance, tools such as HITS [143] and ChatTester [161] prompt the LLM to first summarize the core functionality of the method under test, then enumerate all possible test scenarios with a focus on boundary conditions, and finally generate specific test code for each scenario.",
    "Task decomposition can also be applied to the generation process itself.",
    "CasModaTest [99], for example, decomposes the task into generating the test prefix (handling setup and dependencies) followed by the test oracle (handling assertions), which reduces the cognitive complexity associated with single-step generation."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "For instance, tools such as HITS [143] and ChatTester [161] prompt the LLM to first summarize the core functionality of the method under test, then enumerate all possible test scenarios with a focus on boundary conditions, and finally generate specific test code for each scenario.",
    "CasModaTest [99], for example, decomposes the task into generating the test prefix (handling setup and dependencies) followed by the test oracle (handling assertions), which reduces the cognitive complexity associated with single-step generation."
  ]
